TEXT: The applicant , PERSON , is a NORP national who was born in DATE and lives in NORP . She is represented before the ORG by Mr I. K. Yıldırım and PERSON , lawyers practising in GPE .
The facts of the case , as submitted by the parties , may be summarised as follows .

On DATE ORG and Highways expropriated a part of a plot of land ( plot no . CARDINAL ) belonging to the applicant in GPE . A committee of experts had assessed the value of the land and an amount of compensation was paid to the applicant at the time of the expropriation .
On DATE the applicant filed a case with ORG and requested additional compensation .
On DATE ORG awarded the applicant additional compensation of MONEY ( TRL ) ( MONEY ( ORG ) ) plus interest at the statutory rate , running from DATE .
On DATE ORG upheld the judgment of the firstinstance court .

The applicant commenced enforcement proceedings . On DATE the administration paid the applicant the amount of TRL CARDINAL ( approximately EUR CARDINAL ) covering additional compensation and interest , as well as costs and expenses .
The relevant domestic law and practice in force at the material time are outlined in the Gül and Others v. GPE ( ( dec . ) , no . DATE , DATE ) .
